SHIP
  List your ships in a human-readable table.

SYNTAX
  ship [<ship-spec>][?realm=N][&type=X]
  shp  [<ship-spec>][?realm=N][&type=X]

DESCRIPTION
  Displays a table of ships you own.  With no argument shows all
  your ships.

  <ship-spec> - a uid, uid range, comma list, "*" for all, "~" for
                ships with no fleet assigned, or a fleet letter (see
                'info fleetadd').  Note that "#N" here means uid N
                (not a realm), same as navigate/fire/torpedo.

  Two optional filters can be appended after '?' (and combined with
  '&'), matching the sector-spec '?condition' convention (info realm):

    ?realm=N    - only ships currently within realm N's bounding box
                  (see 'info realm'; ships use ?realm=N rather than
                  #N, since #N already means "uid N" here)
    ?type=X     - only ships of type X -- matches the short type
                  code shown in 'show ship' (e.g. "can" for nuc
                  carrier) or a case-insensitive substring of the
                  full name (e.g. "carrier")

  Column meanings:
    shp#      - ship uid (used in load, unload, navigate, etc.)
    ship type - name of ship type (frigate, destroyer, etc.)
    x,y       - current location (relative to your capital)
    fl        - fleet letter (~ means not in a fleet; see 'info fleetadd'
                to assign ships to a fleet and use the letter as a
                group selector on navigate/fire/torpedo/tend)
    eff       - efficiency 0-100%.  Ships sink if efficiency drops to 0
    civ       - civilians on board
    mil       - military on board
    uw        - uncompensated workers on board
    fd        - food on board
    pn        - planes on board
    he        - helicopters on board
    xl        - extra-light planes on board
    ln        - land units on board
    mob       - mobility points
    tech      - tech level the ship was built at

EXAMPLE
  ship *                    all your ships
  ship 0                    ship number 0 only
  ship 0-5                  ships 0 through 5
  ship *?realm=2            all ships within realm 2
  ship *?type=can           all nuc carriers, wherever they are
  ship *?realm=2&type=can   nuc carriers within realm 2 only

